            </div>
            <h5 class="university-selection-title">Application steps for international candidate</h5>
            <div class="university-selection-text"><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 1</span>: Register your application at Innopolis university application portal https://apply.innopolis.ru/en/get-in/ . Fill in the application form, pass online tests and submit your application.</p><p><br /></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 2</span>: Get an invitation to the next round of the Contest and go through it.</p><p><br /></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 3</span>: Receive the Contest results and the scholarship offer.</p><p><br /></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Step 4</span>: Provide your enrollment and visa documents and come to Innopolis in mid-August.<br /></p></div>
            <a class="university-selection-btn" href="https://apply.innopolis.ru/en/get-in/" target="_blank">Apply</a>
        </div>
        <a class="important-topics-for-entrants-tab" id="faq-for-entrants"><span class="important-topics-for-entrants-tab__text">F.A.Q.</span> <i class="icon-ic_arrow_right-small"></i></a>
        <div class="important-topics-for-entrants-tab-result faq__result" id="faq-for-entrants__result" style="display: none;">
            <div><div class="faq-info-block">
                    <h2 class="faq-info-block__title">How to enter Innopolis University as an international student?</h2>
                    <div class="faq-info-block__text"><p>Apply at Innopolis university application portal https://apply.innopolis.ru/en/get-in/ . On the results of Scholarship Contest the candidates are offered:</p><p><br /></p><p>1. 100% Scholarship. Grant (Scholarship) covers tuition fee and monthly allowance (up to 36000 RUB and depends on academic performance and extra-curriculum activity).</p><p>2. Partial  Scholarship: 25%, 50% or 75% tuition fee discount. <br /></p></div>
                </div><div class="faq-info-block">
                    <h2 class="faq-info-block__title">What language must be used in application documents?</h2>
                    <div class="faq-info-block__text"><p>CV, Motivation letter and other documents must be written in English. If any documents are issued not in English, please provide translation into Russian (can be not notarized). Secondary School Certificate/Diploma and Transcript are provided in the original language. </p></div>
                </div></div>
            <a href="https://apply.innopolis.university/en/faq/" class="faq-info-btn" target="_blank">More questions</a>
